Procedural_Guidance.Question: Customer De-escalation Strategies.
Procedural_Guidance.Answer:
Acknowledge the customer situation:I am really sorry we have put this pressure on you.I completely understand what it is like to have other priorities and want to provide for your family.Just give me a moment and let me see if we can work this out.Pro-tip: It is not absolutely necessary to say,I am sorry, it does go a long way and it is the best way to communicate empathy as well as acknowledgement.
2. Guide the customer, and provide solutions:We really want to partner with you you. Would you prefer other method of communications.I recognize you are doing the best you can.Pro-tip: Before suggesting any solution, confirm the customer records that this isn,t a common occurrence or that any of the current settlements are already at risk.
